'''Alesso''' nɣ d '''Alessio Baldovinetti''' (14 ktubeṛ 1425 - 29 ɣuct 1499), ikka tt nn iga yan umkla [[Ṭṭalyan|aṭalyan]] n Tlslalit tazaykut.

==Tasknudrt==

Ilul-d Baldovinetti ɣ [[Flurinsa]] dar yat tawja n "nobles" igan tansbaɣurt. Asggʷas n 1448, ittuzmmem am yan sɣ igmamn n Guild n St. Luke (Agʷrram Luke): "Alesso di Baldovinetti, dipintore."

Ikka-t-inn iga amḍfar n tgrumma-ann n imẓrilawn imassann d yimẓrfamamn n tẓuri ɣ ar ittamu Andrea del Castagno, Paolo Uccello nttan d Domenico Veneziano.  F ɣaylli ittyawnnan, nttan ad yawsn ɣ usdikuṛ n tglizt n S. Egidio, is hlli ur iɣama kra n record ma s ad tssnẓut taɣawsa-ad. Ttyawskarn idikuṛn-ad ɣ isggʷasn n 1441 - 1451 s tkssa n Domenico Veneziano d Andrea del Castagno. Aylli iffuɣ ccekk, iga-t mas d nttan ad ittyukllafn s usmad-nns ɣ yan usakud igan aḍfran (1460).

Asggʷas n 1426, ittusmahl Alesso s tklut n ufrisku ixatrn i "Annunciation" ɣ ammas n tɣzamt n Annunziata tabaziliyt. Isagurn mklli s ar tn-nttannay, gan yan wanẓa f tsugrt n unaẓur ɣ usrws n yifruritn igamann s trarit-nns n tɣḍʷft inɣdn bahra, taɣawsa nna yujjan Vasari ad fll-as izmmem yat snat tguriwin di-s zdinin : "Ikka-t-inn iɛzza dar-s ad yamẓ timuɣliwin issnɣl-tnt nnican mkdda gant ɣ ugama-nnsnt, d mkann maf ar ilmma nttannay ɣ tflwin-nns isaffn; tilggʷin, iẓran, imɣayn, igumma, iɣarasn, igran, timdinin, d wahli n tɣawsiwin-yaḍnin mi ur ili ttmi," ikka-t-inn awd iga yan "inveterate experimentalist" ɣ iskkinn itiqniyn.
